THE PILOT WAS ATTEMPTING TO LAND A HEAVILY LOADED DE HAVILLAND OTTER 
(DHC-3) ON A GRAVEL STRIP IN RURAL ALASKA. UPON TOUCHDOWN,  THE PILOT 
REPORTED THAT THE AIRPLANE VEERED SLIGHTLY TO THE RIGHT. HE UNLOCKED 
THE TAIL WHEEL CENTERING DEVICE AND ATTEMPTED TO CORRECT TO THE LEFT 
(INTO THE PREVAILING CROSSWIND). THE AIRPLANE CONTINUED TO THE LEFT OUT 
OF CONTROL AND DOWN A 30-45 DEGREE EMBANKMENT BEFORE COMING TO A 
STOP. 
